If you are sick, have someone sick in your home, and/or are self-isolating you need to wash your laundry thoroughly:
  • Contaminated laundry should be placed in a laundry basket with a plastic liner.
  • Wear gloves and mask when handling.
  • Wash with regular laundry soap and hot water (60-90Â°C)
  • Clean your hands with soap and water immediately after removing your gloves.
If you are not ill you should continue to practice physical distancing and be sure to clean and disinfect frequently touched objects, material and surfaces
